FBIS4-39910 "drsov113_a_94022" FBIS-SOV-94-113 Daily Report 12 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Armenia Supports Russian Plan on Karabakh Conflict Armenia Supports Russian Plan on Karabakh Conflict LD1206014594 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0100 GMT 12 Jun 94 LD1206014594 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Russian BFN [Text] The head of the Armenian parliament, Babken Ararktsyan, who is visiting Moscow, said he supported Russia's plan for the settlement of the Armenian-Azerbaijani conflict. In Ararktsyan's words, the position taken by Armenia fully coincides with the Russian position. Its main points are a cease-fire in the conflict zone, the disengagement of the warring sides and the introduction of the CIS peacekeeping forces into the buffer zone. These measures are designed to create conditions for resolving the status of Nagorno-Karabakh.
